<text xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="Fluid_Reading_Text"><body><div change="#StB" n="29" type="r"><sp who="#V."><p><pb facs="#f030"/><milestone facs="#f030_z000" n="30" unit="folio_number"/><lb/>for all their much-boasted science<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add><lb/> has had the ordinary courage to tell <lb/>us. Whatever was his name <del change="#StBa" facs="#f030_z001" hand="#Wilde" rend="single-stroke">and </del><add change="#StBa" facs="#f030_z002" hand="#Wilde" place="above" rend="no_caret">or </add>race, <lb/>he <del change="#StD" facs="#f030_z003" hand="#Wilde">was </del>certainly <add change="#StD" facs="#f030_z003" hand="#Wilde" place="intentions">was </add>the true founder of<lb/> social intercourse. <del change="#StB" facs="#f030_z004" hand="#Wilde" rend="multi-stroke">As we k </del>For the <lb/>aim of the <add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z005" hand="#comp" place="nc">l</add><del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z005" hand="#comp">L</del>iar is simply to charm,<lb/> to delight, to give pleasure. He is <lb/>the very basis of civili<del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z006" hand="#comp">z</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z006" hand="#comp" place="nc"><del change="#StD" facs="#f030_z006" hand="#comp">s</del></add><add change="#StD" facs="#f030_z006" hand="#Wilde" place="intentions">z</add>ed society, and<lb/> without him a dinner party<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> even at<lb/> the mansions of the great<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> is as dull<lb/> as a lecture at the Royal Society<del change="#StC" hand="#comp">,</del><add change="#StD" hand="#comp" place="intentions">,</add><note rend="small">78</note> or <lb/>a debate at the Incorporated Authors<add change="#StD" facs="#f030_z007" hand="#Wilde" place="intentions">, or one of Mr Burnand's farcical comedies</add>.<del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z007" hand="#comp">"</del><note rend="small">79</note><lb/></p>
					<p><add change="#StD" place="intentions">"</add><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc"><del change="#StD" hand="#comp">'</del></add><del change="#StC" hand="#comp">"</del>Nor will he be welcomed<lb/> by <del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z008" hand="#comp">S</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z008" hand="#comp" place="nc">s</add>ociety alone. Art, breaking from the <lb/>prison-house of <del change="#StAb" facs="#f030_z010" hand="#Wilde">Realism and abandoning the </del><add change="#StA" hand="#Wilde" place="berg"><del change="#StAb" facs="#f030_z010" hand="#Wilde">wicked </del></add><del change="#StAb" facs="#f030_z010" hand="#Wilde">tents of those peripatetic photographers who call them-selves Naturalistic novelists </del><del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z009" hand="#comp">R</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z009" hand="#comp" place="nc">r</add>ealism,<note rend="small">80</note> will run to <lb/>greet him<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> and will kiss his false<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> <lb/>beautiful lips, knowing that he alone<lb/> is in possession of the great secret<lb/> of all her manifestations, the secret <lb/>that <del change="#StD" facs="#f030_z011">t</del><add change="#StD" facs="#f030_z011" place="intentions">T</add>ruth is entirely and absolutely<lb/> a matter of style<del change="#StD" facs="#f030_z012">.</del><add change="#StD" facs="#f030_z012" place="intentions">;</add><note rend="small">81</note> <del change="#StD" facs="#f030_z012">w</del><add change="#StD" facs="#f030_z012" place="intentions">W</add>hile Life<del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z013" hand="#comp">,</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z013" hand="#comp" place="nc">--</add>poor<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> <lb/>probable<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> uninteresting <add change="#StB" facs="#f030_z015" hand="#Wilde" place="inline">human </add><del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z014" hand="#comp">L</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z014" hand="#comp" place="nc">l</add>ife<del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z014" hand="#comp">,</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z014" hand="#comp" place="nc">--</add><lb/>tired of repeating herself for the<lb/> benefit of Mr<del change="#StC" hand="#comp">.</del><add change="#StD" place="intentions">.</add>Herbert Spencer,<note rend="small">82</note> scientific<lb/> historians, and the compilers of statistics<lb/> in general,<note rend="small">83</note> will follow meekly after<lb/> him, and try to reproduce<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> in her own<lb/> simple and untutored way<add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> some of the<lb/> marvels of which he talks.<del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z016" hand="#comp">"</del> <lb/></p>
					<p><add change="#StD" place="intentions">"</add><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc"><del change="#StD" hand="#comp">'</del></add><del change="#StC" hand="#comp">"</del>No doubt there will always be critics<lb/> who, <add change="#StB" facs="#f030_z017" hand="#Wilde" place="inline">like a certain writer in the</add><lb/><add change="#StB" facs="#f030_z018" hand="#Wilde" place="inline"><hi rend="italic">Saturday Review</hi>,</add> will gravely censure<lb/> the <del change="#StAb" facs="#f030_z019" hand="#Wilde">writer </del><add change="#StB" facs="#f030_z019" hand="#Wilde" place="inline">teller </add>of <del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z020" hand="#comp">F</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z020" hand="#comp" place="nc">f</add>airy <del change="#StC" facs="#f030_z020" hand="#comp">T</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f030_z020" hand="#comp" place="nc">t</add>ales for his defective<note rend="small">84</note></p>
				</sp>
			</div>
			<div change="#StB" n="30" type="r">
				<sp who="#V.">
					<p/></sp></div></body></text>